The paper discusses a hardware accelerator for RNNs, which falls under the category of embedded systems (cs.ET) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also mentions the use of the Chipmunk accelerator for voice-based human-machine interfaces, which could fall under the categories of audio and speech processing (cs.SY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the Chipmunk architecture in a systolic array, which could fall under the category of parallel and distributed computing (cs.DC) or computer architecture (cs.AR).
